<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Rich 12-bar evening hymn. "33" and "43" inversions. G=①, Am=②m, Em=③m, C=④, D=⑤.
- Non-diatonic: E7 → Em (③m), A7 → Am (②m), Eb → nearest diatonic (Em or D).
- CΔ7 → C (④). Bm7 → ③m (Bm). All SSAATTBB voices merged into 3 staves.
- LH 4-note open. RH 2-note thirds/sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 2, 8: C-G rocking (IV-I) with common tone E3 in LH held across.
- Bars 7-8: stepwise bass descent E2→D2→A2→E2, mirrors the descending melodic arc.
- Bar 11: Em→G (③m→①) common tone G3 in LH held.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opens with a rising melodic line. Climax bars 9-10 (D5 melody high point).
- Second half (bars 7-12) mirrors first half structurally. Final D-G cadence bar 12.
-->
